abstract: Unlike predecessors who traveled to the United States before rising to the papacy, Pope Francis has waited until age 78 to visit the country that thinks of itself as the center of everything.
snippet: Unlike predecessors who traveled to the United States before rising to the papacy, Pope Francis has waited until age 78 to visit the country that thinks of itself as the center of everything.
lead_paragraph: During his first private meeting with Pope Francis in the Vatican two years ago, Cardinal Timothy M. Dolan said, the pope took out an atlas with a map of the United States and asked Cardinal Dolan, the archbishop of New York, to point out the various regions and cities and talk about how they differed.

abstract: The state is caught up in a clash between oil and environmental interests, and the issues are so thorny that even Democratic leaders are on opposing sides.
snippet: The state is caught up in a clash between oil and environmental interests, and the issues are so thorny that even Democratic leaders are on opposing sides.
lead_paragraph: SACRAMENTO — With President Obama back from a trip to Alaska in which he portrayed the fight against climate change as an urgent international priority, California is showing how hard it can be — even in a state overwhelmingly controlled by Democrats — to get an ambitious carbon reduction bill passed.

abstract: A review of Duncan Macmillan’s new play “People, Places and Things.”
snippet: A review of Duncan Macmillan’s new play “People, Places and Things.”
lead_paragraph: Toward the end of Duncan Macmillan’s “People, Places and Things,” a portrait of a skeptic in the church of Alcoholics Anonymous, I began to think that I had misjudged it. At that point, the scene had shifted from the rehab center, where most of the work is set, to the childhood home of the show’s central figure for the expected day of reckoning with Mom and Dad.

abstract: My parents’ approach to death reflected their marriage: He always needed control, while she let events shape her.

lead_paragraph: My parents each took an approach to the end of life that was indicative of the way they lived their lives.

abstract: You may have talked with your children about drinking. But have you talked about the way teenagers really drink?
snippet: You may have talked with your children about drinking. But have you talked about the way teenagers really drink?
lead_paragraph: As a parent, you’ve probably talked to your young children about alcohol (“See this drink I’m having? It’s not for you”) and to teenagers about drinking (“Don’t do it, and if you do don’t drive, and did I ever do it? Ooh, look, a woodpecker!”). But have you talked to your children, particularly your high schoolers and soon-to-be college students, about drinking the way it’s often done at that age — hard, fast, and with the intent of getting drunk?

abstract: A guide to movies playing at theaters in the New York City area, as well as select festivals and film series. A complete list of new releases is at nytimes.com/intheaters.

lead_paragraph: Ratings and running times are in parentheses; foreign films have English subtitles. Full reviews of all current releases: nytimes.com/movies.

abstract: With an upgraded structure, a reduction in noise and more, the 2016 model is a far better truck than the one it replaces.
snippet: With an upgraded structure, a reduction in noise and more, the 2016 model is a far better truck than the one it replaces.
lead_paragraph: THE Toyota Tacoma’s reputation for reliability is legendary, but after a decade without major changes, the truck had become a bit long in the tooth. Yet it owned the midsize pickup market, with the Nissan Frontier and Honda Ridgeline far behind.
headline_main: Video Review: Toyota Tacoma Adds Machismo, but Retains Its Reliability
headline_print_headline: An Upgraded Toyota Tacoma Adds Machismo, but Retains Its Reliability
